cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks for radiomics-based lung cancer detection using CT imaging data, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed framework involves the use of machine learning techniques to discover custom radiomic sequencers for lung cancer detection.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves the use of AI techniques such as deep learning for radiomics-based lung cancer detection.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the use of radiomics-based features for characterizing lung tumour phenotype, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval from medical images.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves the use of CT imaging data for lung cancer detection, which can be seen as a form of multimedia analysis.
